(48,1,1,'2015-01-15 02:38:14','In the studio with Sam Mcgarrigle','<p><img id=\"blog_image_48\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam1.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>One of the major highlights during the recent festivities, if not the whole of last year, was a last-minute opportunity to spend some time with Sam Mcgarrigle AKA Gross Magic and see first hand what the devil he had been up to recently. &nbsp;A small studio close by to Brighton&rsquo;s Green Door Store was booked the evening before Xmas eve and I felt very lucky to be able to sit in and get the sense that I was ending the year on a pretty awesomely privileged high. &nbsp;To be one of the first people to hear live versions of some of Sam&rsquo;s new songs that may very well be performed soon at a venue near you from his first official album and under a rumoured new artistic alias. Hopefully these photos give a sense of the vibe in the room, which was pretty massive. &nbsp;Watch this space.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_50\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam3.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Your friendly autonomous internet radio station. Present but not transmitting.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_51\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam4.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Van Stonholdt on bass. Dreamy.</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_52\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam5.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Sweet vibes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_53\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam6.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_54\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam7.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_55\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam8.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_56\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam9.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_57\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam10.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_58\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam11.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Sam describes drum part.</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_59\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam12.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Socks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_60\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam13.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Shop.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_61\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam14.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_62\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/sam15.jpg&amp;w=940&h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>After the Jam: hanging with Tim\'s cat sir Zootalot.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','sam'),
(49,2,1,'2015-01-17 23:39:35','Human Nature','<p>The band Human Nature, originally from West Sussex, will be hitting up a close circle of friends in south London this time next week with their premiere live performance and we can\'t help ourselves but be rooting and tooting over this imminent epochal moment. &nbsp;Here are some quick shots of the band and a quick promo video we threw together based on some rehearsal vibes that went down a couple of weeks ago, just as we entered the new year, from the band\'s newly established fucking sweet jam zone.</p>\r\n<p>Look out for more from these guys soon.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/t1XxeS-wVFA\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p class=\"embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9\">Euan, Del, Tom and Ben AKA Human Nature.</p>\r\n<p><img id=\"blog_image_67\" class=\"center img-responsive\" src=\"/tt/tt.php?src=./uploads/hnposter.jpg&amp;w=940&amp;h=\" alt=\"\" /></p>','humannature'),
(50,2,1,'2015-07-31 08:36:31','Family Vibes','<p>[blog-image:eyJpZCI6OTIsImJsb2dfaWQiOjUwLCJmaWxlbmFtZSI6IkRTQ0YwODQyX18xLmpwZyIsImltYWdlX3dpZHRoIjpudWxsLCJpbWFnZV9oZWlnaHQiOm51bGwsInNpemUiOiIiLCJmbHVpZCI6ImltZy1mbHVpZCIsImNlbnRlcmVkIjoiIiwiY2FwdGlvbiI6IiJ9]</p>\r\n<p>I spent the afternoon with the two humans known as Sam McGarrigle and Ben Waggett (from Human Nature). I had driven us into to town because I was determined to get some small parts to fix up Ben\'s acoustic guitar and we ended up at Brighton marina where it turned into an opportune moment for a quick photo shoot using the camera that was paid for using Bitcoins. Here\'s to short excursions by the sea. For a moment it felt like a holiday.</p>\r\n<p>[blog-image:eyJpZCI6ODUsImJsb2dfaWQiOjUwLCJmaWxlbmFtZSI6IkRTQ0YwODI5X18xLmpwZyIsImltYWdlX3dpZHRoIjpudWxsLCJpbWFnZV9oZWlnaHQiOm51bGwsInNpemUiOiIiLCJmbHVpZCI6ImltZy1mbHVpZCIsImNlbnRlcmVkIjoiIiwiY2FwdGlvbiI6IiJ9]</p>\r\n<p>[blog-image:eyJpZCI6OTAsImJsb2dfaWQiOjUwLCJmaWxlbmFtZSI6IkRTQ0YwODQwX18xLmpwZyIsImltYWdlX3dpZHRoIjpudWxsLCJpbWFnZV9oZWlnaHQiOm51bGwsInNpemUiOiIiLCJmbHVpZCI6ImltZy1mbHVpZCIsImNlbnRlcmVkIjoiIiwiY2FwdGlvbiI6IiJ9]</p>\r\n<p>[blog-image:eyJpZCI6OTEsImJsb2dfaWQiOjUwLCJmaWxlbmFtZSI6IkRTQ0YwODQxX18xLmpwZyIsImltYWdlX3dpZHRoIjpudWxsLCJpbWFnZV9oZWlnaHQiOm51bGwsInNpemUiOiIiLCJmbHVpZCI6ImltZy1mbHVpZCIsImNlbnRlcmVkIjoiIiwiY2FwdGlvbiI6IiJ9]</p>\r\n<p>[blog-image:eyJpZCI6OTMsImJsb2dfaWQiOjUwLCJmaWxlbmFtZSI6IkRTQ0YwODQzX18xLmpwZyIsImltYWdlX3dpZHRoIjpudWxsLCJpbWFnZV9oZWlnaHQiOm51bGwsInNpemUiOiIiLCJmbHVpZCI6ImltZy1mbHVpZCIsImNlbnRlcmVkIjoiIiwiY2FwdGlvbiI6IiJ9]</p>','behindthescenes'),
